    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-04-24</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-07-24T14:08:10Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Orphan Works Act of 2008 - Limits the remedies in a civil action brought for infringement of copyright in an orphan work if the infringer proves that: (1) the infringer performed and documented a reasonably diligent search in good faith to locate the copyright owner before using the work, but was unable to locate the owner; (2) a Notice of Use was filed with the Register of Copyrights before the work was used; and (3) the infringing use of the work provided attribution to the owner of the copyright, if known. </p> <p>Permits an award of reasonable compensation for the use of the infringed work, except if: (1) the infringement is performed without any commercial advantage and for primarily a charitable, religious, scholarly, or educational purpose; and (2) the infringer ceases the infringement expeditiously after receiving notice of the claim for infringement.</p> <p>Directs the Register of Copyrights to: (1) undertake a certification process for the establishment of an electronic database to facilitate the search for pictorial, graphic, and sculptural works that are subject to copyright protection; and (2) study and report to Congress on remedies for copyright infringement claims by an individual copyright owner or a related group of copyright owners seeking small amounts of monetary relief.</p> <p>Directs the Comptroller General to study and report to Congress on the function of the deposit requirement in the copyright registration system .</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
